<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUSH PITCHING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As President Bush throws out the first ball signifying the start of the 
baseball season and our national pastime, let us all hope that when the World 
Series rolls around and George sits down about that time to talk to Mikhail 
Gorbachev that he manages to hold his own in the "World Serious" talks. 
</P>
<P>
We certainly can't afford a "Bush League" performance when he makes that 
"pitch." 
</P>
<P>
WILLIAM KRAUSE 
</P>
<P>
Palm Springs 
</P>
