<HEADLINE>
<P>
POINTS OF LIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a father, one of the daily rituals I cherish most is reading to my kids. My 
6 year old is currently on his second excursion through the "Chronicles of 
Narnia," by C.S. Lewis. The sixth installment of the "Chronicles" is entitled 
"The Magician's Nephew," wherein we encountered the following: "One moment 
there had been nothing but darkness; next moment a thousand, thousand points of 
light leaped out." 
</P>
<P>
So now we know what George Bush's speech writers read -- kiddie lit. At least 
it's good kiddie lit, and my estimation of our President's staff has been 
elevated a notch. 
</P>
<P>
J.S. KLEINSASSER 
</P>
<P>
Bakersfield 
</P>
</TEXT>
