<P>
MGM/UA Television and Soyuztelefilm will co-produce a four-hour television 
miniseries about a joint Soviet-U.S. space expedition to Mars. The production, 
for NBC in this country and Gosteleradio in the Soviet Union, will be filmed 
primarily in the Soviet Union and will be a collaborative effort of Soviet and 
American writers, directors and actors. Executive producers from the United 
States are Lawrence Horowitz and David Gerber, chairman of MGM/UA Television. 
Filming is expected to begin next spring. ALEENE MacMINN 
