<HEADLINE>
<P>
USEFUL TIPS ON BANANAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Here are some useful tips on bananas: 
</P>
<P>
 -- Bananas will ripen more quickly if placed in a brown paper bag and held at 
room temperature. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Banana garnish: Run the prongs of a fork lengthwise down a peeled banana 
then slice crosswise for dainty crinkly edged rounds. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Coat sliced banana for salads with lemon juice to keep from browning. 
Orange or pineapple juice is also good and adds a pleasant flavor. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Toast thick banana bread slices and top with peanut butter and jelly for a 
quick breakfast with a glass of milk. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Freeze a banana in its peel. Thaw slightly, peel and slice into dessert 
dish and drizzle with a teaspoon of maple syrup. A wonderful low-calorie 
dessert. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Bananas pack easily in brown-bag lunches. They come in their own wrapping 
and need no further preparation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
