WIDOW OF HIROHITO VISITS HIS TOMB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Empress Dowager Nagako, Emperor Hirohito's widow, visited her husband's tomb 
for the first time Wednesday in her first trip outside the Imperial Palace in 
nearly seven months, a palace official said. 
</P>
<P>
The 86-year-old empress dowager rode in a passenger car from the Imperial 
Palace in Tokyo to Hirohito's hillside mausoleum in Hachioji about 30 miles 
away. She walked several yards to the tomb with the help of an aide. Emperor 
Hirohito died of cancer Jan. 7 at age 87. His widow did not attend the 
ceremonies because of ill health. 
