SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rolando Ignacio, accused of attempting to kill three people on a downtown San 
Diego street Nov. 22, was ruled mentally incompetent and not fit to stand 
trial. 
</P>
<P>
Ignacio will be sent to Patton State Mental Hospital near San Bernardino, where 
he will receive psychiatric treatment. 
</P>
<P>
Ignacio is accused of shooting into a crowd of people at 4th Avenue and Market 
Street downtown. He wounded Robert Mengar, 59, and Mengar's fiancee, Cynthia 
Conyiers, 37, both of whom had just left a Lions Club luncheon, and Susan 
Snyder, 29, owner of Gaslamp Art Gallery. 
