<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FIRE DAMAGES REPAIR SHOP IN SEPULVEDA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An electrical fire erupted in a Sepulveda transmission repair shop early 
Wednesday, causing $130,000 in damage to the structure and its contents, fire 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out about 3:40 a.m. at Steve's Automatic Transmission Service in 
the 9000 block of Sepulveda Boulevard, said Jim Wells, Los Angeles Fire 
Department spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
It took 45 firefighters about 30 minutes to extinguish the blaze, Wells said. 
There were no injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Six cars stored in the repair shop were partially damaged by the fire, which 
Wells said was caused by an electrical short inside the building. 
</P>
</TEXT>
