<TEXT>
<P>
Freshman third baseman Denny Vigo hit a two-run home run in the top of the 
ninth inning to lead Cal State Northridge to a 4-2 nonconference victory over 
host Fresno State on Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge improved to 19-11-1. Fresno State, ranked 12th in Division I by 
Collegiate Baseball magazine, is 27-13. 
</P>
<P>
Senior left-hander Fili Martinez (4-3) pitched his third consecutive complete 
game, allowing six hits and striking out eight. 
</P>
<P>
Fresno State took a 2-1 lead in the sixth on Steve Vondran's two-out single 
that scored Tom Goodwin, who extended his hitting streak to 28 games with a 
bunt single. 
</P>
<P>
Chae-Ho Chong led off the sixth with his eighth home run of the season to make 
the score, 2-2, setting the stage for Vigo's home run off Fresno State bullpen 
ace Bobby Jones that drove in Rusty McLain. 
