<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: CS NORTHRIDGE SIGNS FOUR SOFTBALL PLAYERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Northridge softball team is using Crescenta Valley High the way a 
major league baseball team takes advantage of a its minor league system. 
</P>
<P>
The Lady Matadors, who already have five former Crescenta Valley players on 
their roster, will add another next season. 
</P>
<P>
Gina Moe, a two-year starter at second base for the Falcons, has orally 
commited to play softball for Northridge. She said Wednesday that she will sign 
a letter of intent as soon as it arrives in the mail. 
</P>
<P>
Also committing to CSUN was Lisa Ferraconi, a catcher from Palomar College; 
Danielle Wood, a first baseman from Hart High; and Lisa Huffaker, a shortstop 
from El Camino Real High who has been a starter on two City Section 
championship teams. 
</P>
<P>
As expected, Cal State Northridge signed three basketball recruits -- all from 
Northern California -- to letters of intent Wednesday. Signing were Al Jackson, 
a 6-1 guard from West Valley College, Shanan Rosenberg, a 6-8 forward from St. 
Francis High and Percy Fisher, a 6-7 forward from San Francisco Riordan High. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson averaged 11 points and 5.5 assists for West Valley in 1988. He 
redshirted last season. Rosenberg averaged 16 points and 12 rebounds and Fisher 
eight points and six rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
The Men's Senior Baseball League of Los Angeles and Ventura counties opens play 
this weekend with a doubleheader at Bluebird Field in Sun Valley. 
</P>
<P>
The four-team league for players 30-and-over includes a 15-game schedule and a 
double-elimination tournament in September. 
</P>
<P>
Ed Gran, a former Cal Lutheran offensive coordinator and wide receiver coach, 
has been hired as a graduate assistant football coach at Southeast Missouri 
State in Cape Girardeau, Mo. Gran played for Cal Lutheran before becoming wide 
receiver coach in 1987 and offensive coordinator last season. 
</P>
<P>
Coach Bob Shoup is interviewing applicants for the offensive coordinator 
position. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<CORRECTION-DATE>
<P>
April 14, 1989, Friday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</CORRECTION-DATE>
<CORRECTION>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
<P>
A headline in Thursday's Valley sports section incorrectly reported the status 
of four Cal State Northridge softball recruits. 
</P>
<P>
The recruits so far have given only oral commitments to CSUN Coach Gary 
Torgeson. 
</P>
</CORRECTION>
