<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 3 HELD IN KILLING OF 'GOOD SAMARITAN' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles police have arrested three of four youths suspected in the April 2 
killing of a North Hollywood man who chased the group after they tried to steal 
a neighbor's pickup truck. 
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old alleged triggerman and a 17-year-old companion were arrested at 
a home in North Hollywood, and the third suspect, also 16, was arrested while 
walking along a street in the community, Lt. Ron LaRue said. 
</P>
<P>
The teen-agers were booked on suspicion of murder and were being held without 
bail at Sylmar Juvenile Hall. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators are looking for a fourth juvenile in the shooting of Darris 
Garvin, 37, who apparently surprised the youths as they were attempting to 
steal a pickup truck that belonged to another tenant of his apartment complex. 
Garvin chased them for a block before one shot him in the abdomen, police said. 
</P>
<P>
"He was just an innocent Good Samaritan," LaRue said. "And he ends up paying 
the ultimate price." 
</P>
</TEXT>
