<TEXT>
<P>
Soviet arms control inspectors decided to conduct "short-notice" inspections at 
Cape Canaveral, Fla., and Huntsville, Ala., under terms of the treaty banning 
medium-range nuclear weapons, the Pentagon announced. The Soviet inspection 
teams had arrived in Washington on Tuesday. Cmdr. Ken Pease, a Pentagon 
spokesman, said one 10-member team specified a visit to a missile storage 
facility at the Redstone Army Depot in Huntsville. The other 10-member team 
asked to inspect Complex 16 at Patrick Air Force Base near Cape Canaveral. 
Complex 16 was once used as a launch test center for the Pershing 2 and 
ground-launched cruise missiles that are covered by the treaty. 
</P>
