<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOVIET DEFECTOR TO SPEAK IN OXNARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vladimir Sakharov, often called the key Soviet defector in the United States, 
and Ambassador Philip C. Habib, who has served four presidents, will be the 
featured guest speakers at a program presented May 9 by Ventura County National 
Bank in Oxnard Civic Auditorium. 
</P>
<P>
The son of a KGB courier, Sakharov was a high-ranking Soviet diplomat prior to 
his defection. He is now one of the leading U.S. experts on Soviet policy 
objectives and intelligence gathering. 
</P>
<P>
Habib has participated in many international peace negotiations. He is a 
30-year diplomat whose negotiations with the late Anwar Sadat of Egypt and 
Menachem Begin of Israel cleared the way for the Camp David summit during the 
Carter Administration. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets for the 7:30 p.m. event will be available to the public Tuesday. Prices 
are $15, $20 and $25 and include admission to a buffet reception honoring 
Sakharov and Habib following the program. For information, call (805) 656-4621. 
</P>
</TEXT>
