<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: CULVER CITY; 
</P>
<P>
PARKING ORDINANCE CHANGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council this week introduced and approved an interim ordinance that 
requires developers to provide 3.5 parking spaces for three-bedroom units in 
multifamily dwellings. 
</P>
<P>
The ordinance is effective immediately and replaces a similar ordinance 
approved last fall that mandated 2.5 parking spaces for three-bedroom units. 
</P>
<P>
Councilman Steven Gourley, who asked for the stricter limits, said many 
three-bedroom apartments are rented by groups of adults, who tend to have more 
cars, than by families with young children. 
</P>
