<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: PACIFIC PALISADES; 
</P>
<P>
HOUSING HEIGHT LIMITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles City Council's Planning Committee will consider a motion to 
limit multiresidential housing heights citywide to 35 feet on May 11, 
Councilman Marvin Braude said. 
</P>
<P>
Harold Waterhouse of Pacific Palisades organized a community campaign in 
support of stricter height limits last year after a 71-foot condominium was 
build on Sunset Boulevard near his home on Wildomar Street. Waterhouse received 
a Golden Sparkplug award from the Palisades community council for his efforts. 
</P>
<P>
Braude said the council may vote on the ordinance this summer. Braude said that 
if the ordinance does not pass, he will reintroduce it for implementation in 
the Palisades only. 
</P>
</TEXT>
