<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
KENNEDY'S HANSELL IS PERFECT AGAINST GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Greg Hansell pitched a perfect game as Kennedy High School defeated Garden 
Grove, 4-0, Wednesday in Garden Grove League baseball game at Kennedy. 
</P>
<P>
Hansell (6-1) struck out eight and had only one ball hit into the outfield. 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove had only one batter come close to getting on base. Mike Bickford 
led off the seventh inning with a ground ball down the first-base line. 
However, Kennedy first baseman Pete Montera made a diving stop and flipped the 
ball to Hansell, who was covering first base, for the out. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy (13-4 overall, 4-1 in league play) scored on an error in the fourth for 
a 1-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
The Fighting Irish then scored three in the fifth, two on a single by Ernie 
Franco, who has 27 runs batted in this season. 
</P>
<P>
Montera had two hits, including an RBI single in the fifth. 
</P>
<P>
In other Garden Grove League games: 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta 3, Los Amigos 2 -- Jason Parsons, La Quinta's usual starting catcher, 
made his first start as a pitcher this season and came away with the win at 
home. Parsons hit a two-run homer in the first inning, his fifth home run of 
the season. Joe Russo, who was two for three, scored for La Quinta (14-3-1, 
4-1) in the fourth inning on an error. 
</P>
<P>
Santiago 3, Bolsa Grande 1 -- Winning pitcher Sean McCorry allowed just one run 
despite walking six, allowing five hits and having the Santiago defense commit 
six errors. McCorry (3-3), who had to work out of bases-loaded situations in 
three innings, helped himself by picking off three runners. David Smith was two 
for two with a solo home run for Santiago (5-8-1, 2-3). 
</P>
<P>
In the Angelus League: 
</P>
<P>
Bishop Montgomery 3, Servite 2 (9 innings) -- With the score tied at 1-1 after 
seven innings, Bishop Montgomery (11-4, 2-3) scored two in the top of the ninth 
to take a 3-1 lead. Servite (11-4, 2-3) rallied for a run in the bottom of the 
inning when Ed Crippin, who had been hit by a pitch, scored on Rob Walker's 
single. 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei 5, Bishop Amat 4 -- Jim Kelly and Rob Ickes each had two RBIs for 
Mater Dei (13-3, 4-1) at Bishop Montgomery. Jeff Ciccarella also had an RBI for 
the Monarchs. 
</P>
<P>
In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
Los Alamitos 9, Katella 3 -- Winning pitcher Todd Gragnano, who scattered six 
hits, went three for four with two RBIs to lead Los Alamitos (9-8, 4-2) at 
Boysen Park in Anaheim. Los Alamitos' Doug Kieck and Brian Havens each went 
three for four. The win put Los Alamitos in a three-way tie for first with El 
Dorado and Katella (10-6, 4-2). 
</P>
<P>
El Dorado 11, Loara 1 -- Matt Luke had three hits and two RBIs and Phil Nevin 
had two hits, including a three-run homer, for the Golden Hawks (12-5, 4-2) at 
El Dorado. Pete Janicki (2-1) scattered eight hits and struck out five for the 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
Esperanza 14, Cypress 1 -- Dan Redington had a home run, three RBIs and three 
runs scored for Esperanza (7-4-2, 1-4-1) at Cypress. Jason Perez had three RBIs 
and Keith McDonald two for Esperanza. Roger Weems (1-2) pitched a four-hitter 
for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
Anaheim 11, Magnolia 1 -- Jose Gonzalez had three hits and two RBIs for Anaheim 
(9-8, 5-1) at Magnolia. John Barber and Danny Castro each had three hits and a 
RBI. Castro (2-0) also pitched a three-hitter for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Valencia 7, Brea-Olinda 6 -- Keef Leasure's RBI single capped a three-run rally 
in the bottom of the seventh for the Tigers (9-3, 4-2) at Valencia. Rick Gress 
had two hits and three RBIs for Valencia. 
</P>
<P>
In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
Estancia 9, Saddleback 6 -- Robert Nye, Mark Hartley and Len Herman each had 
two RBIs for Estancia (11-5, 4-2) at Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
Tustin 7, Newport Harbor 0 -- Monte Jones (6-0) pitched a two-hitter, striking 
out nine, for Tustin (10-6, 5-1) at Newport Harbor. Jones also had two hits and 
two RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
University 13, Corona del Mar 9 -- Trent McGinn had three hits and five RBIs 
and Dave Dieter had a home run and two RBIs for University (6-9-1, 3-3) at 
Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley 9, Mission Viejo 6 -- Doug Bame had two hits, including a 
grand slam, for the Cougars (11-5, 4-2) at Capistrano Valley. Bame's grand slam 
in the fourth gave the Cougars a 7-3 lead. David Gullien and Dan Zamora each 
had two hits for Capistrano Valley. Troy Kopp had a two-run homer for Mission 
Viejo (11-4, 4-2). 
</P>
<P>
El Toro 8, Dana Hills 3 -- Chris Sauritch went four for four with a double, two 
RBIs and two runs scored to lead El Toro at home. Sean Drinkwater was three for 
four for El Toro (12-5, 4-2) with three RBIs and a run scored. Winning pitcher 
Rob Johnson pitched a six-hitter. 
</P>
<P>
San Clemente 5, Irvine 4 -- Trailing, 4-2, in the bottom of the sixth, San 
Clemente (1-5) rallied for three runs on two home runs to win at home. Rick 
Brail hit a two-run homer with no outs, and Mike Murphy followed that with a 
solo home run. 
</P>
</TEXT>
