<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RETAILING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Mary Ann Galante, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Just in time for Mother's Day, Tiffany &amp; Co. at South Coast Plaza has begun 
carrying its new perfumed bath collection. 
</P>
<P>
The collection -- which includes five new products -- marks the Fifth Avenue 
jeweler's entree into bath products and extends Tiffany's fragrance line that 
was launched in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
"The fragrance market hasn't grown in terms of consumer-unit sales over the 
last 5 years," said Susan Sussman, Tiffany's vice president of fragrance. "It's 
a very tough, competitive environment. . . . The only way to be successful is 
by being better." 
</P>
<P>
Of course, new products can also bring new customers. 
</P>
<P>
Introducing a collection of bath products also makes sense, considering that 
the bath business is more than 25% of the lucrative fragrance industry. 
</P>
<P>
Tiffany's bath-collection line includes scented body creme, body lotion, bath 
and shower gel and dusting powder that comes with a swan's down puff. All of 
them come in square containers that mimic the shape of the Art Deco facade of 
Tiffany's flagship store on Fifth Avenue in Manhattan. 
</P>
<P>
Prices for those "luxury accessories" -- as Tiffany has dubbed them -- range 
from $40 to $75 for 5 ounces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
FRAGRANCES; TIFFANY &amp; CO 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA041389-0172 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 43623 </DOCID>
