<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SOUTH PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
STUDENT WINS STUDY GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pehr Luedtke is one of 66 high school students from across the country selected 
by the National Endowment for the Humanities as a 1989 Younger Scholar. 
</P>
<P>
He will receive a $1,800 grant this summer for independent study on the George 
Donner party, an ill-fated group of 87 pioneers which was stranded without food 
in the Sierra Nevada in the winter of 1946-47. Some members of the group 
resorted to cannibalism. Luedtke said he plans to read diaries left by party 
members and interview experts on the West. 
</P>
<P>
Luedtke, of South Pasadena, attends Polytechnic School in Pasadena. 
</P>
</TEXT>
