<TEXT>
<P>
The southern China city of Canton held its biggest anti-crime rallies in years 
to publicize 28 executions, the official Legal News reported today. 
</P>
<P>
Seventy-four other criminals were given jail sentences at the rallies, which a 
city official said drew over 10,000 people in nine areas of Canton on 
Wednesday. 
