<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
MAN ARRESTED FOR JOSTLING DIANA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man jumped out of a crowd and jostled Princess Diana today during a visit to 
a housing project for the mentally handicapped, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Bodyguards grabbed the man and hustled him away from the Princess of Wales, who 
appeared surprised but was unhurt by the incident in Cramlington, northeast 
England. 
</P>
<P>
Assistant Chief Constable Gordon McMurchie of Northumbria county police told 
reporters the man's motive was not clear and that he was under arrest. 
</P>
<P>
Television news showed the man lunging toward the princess as she shook hands 
with the crowd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
