<P>
FRIEND OF MAYOR BARRY INDICTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charles Lewis, former Virgin Islands official and friend of District of 
Columbia Mayor Marion Barry Jr., was indicted today on 10 felony counts 
stemming from Barry's visits to his hotel room last December. 
</P>
<P>
The grand jury indicted Lewis, who also is facing cocaine possession charges in 
the Virgin Islands, on three counts of cocaine possession and seven counts of 
giving false statements to the grand jury. 
</P>
<P>
The perjury charges center on questions Lewis was asked about visits Barry made 
to his hotel room and what went on there, according to sources close to the 
case. 
</P>
</TEXT>
