<P>
KOHL FIRES DEFENSE MINISTER AND REPLACES 7 OTHER CABINET MEMBERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BONN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chancellor Helmut Kohl today fired his defense minister and replaced seven 
other Cabinet members in an apparent bid to stop his party's declining 
popularity. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to the defense post, Kohl announced a new chief of staff and new 
ministers for finance, interior, transport, economic cooperation, construction 
and information. 
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Rupert Scholz was the only Cabinet member left jobless under 
the changes. He was replaced by Finance Minister Gerhard Stoltenberg. 
</P>
<P>
Kohl said at a news conference that the changes were not a direct consequence 
of his Christian Democratic Union's recent election setbacks, but he conceded 
that his party and coalition government face "a totally new situation." 
</P>
</TEXT>
