P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
FORMICA CORP. OKS MERGER DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WAYNE, N.J. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Formica Corp. announced today it has approved a sweetened merger agreement with 
a management-led investor group which will pay about $365 million in cash for 
the laminated products company. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement does not allow Formica to accept offers from other companies. 
</P>
<P>
The $19-per-share bid by FM Acquisition Corp. includes the assumption of 
Formica debt. Formica announced Monday that it had rejected a $243-million 
takeover from FM Acquisition, one of several offers made for the company in 
recent months. That offer was $18.75 per share. 
</P>
<P>
Formica also announced today that an unidentified industrial corporation, which 
had reportedly offered $20 per share for the company, has withdrawn its offer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
